<p>My aim is to easily edit the .gitignore file corresponding to a particular git local repository (graphically).</p>  <p>I think it would be possible to add a custom action so when we right-click a repository line of the main SourceTree window, it would directly open a text editor with the corresponding repository's .gitignore file. <strong>How to add that custom action?</strong></p>  <p>In fact, i'm surprised there's not already a simple way to do that.</p>